LISBON, Feb. 2 (Xinhua) -- Portugal registered on Wednesday 56 more deaths associated with COVID-19, bringing the national death toll to 20,024, according to the Directorate-General for Health (DGS). The daily epidemiological bulletin shows that there were 54,693 more new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours, bringing the national tally to 2,745,383. According to the Portuguese health authorities, there are 2,442 people in hospital with COVID-19, with 149 of them in intensive care units. Moreover, 33,989 COVID-19 patients were reported to have recovered in the last 24 hours. The DGS also reported that 5,061,810 people have received a COVID-19 vaccine booster shot, and 8,798,287 people have completed primary vaccination, including 301,079 children aged five to 11.  â– 